C
  ==
  - Usually spelt дЄЛ for the above senses
    (i.e. the occurrence classifier and "moment/momentarily" senses).
    This дЄЛ (haa5) is *not* exclusive to Cantonese;
    it is the same дЄЛ (haa5) that is present
    in дЄАдЄЛ (jat1 haa5) and in дЄАдЄЛе≠Р (jat1 haa5 zi2).
    However, the spelling дЄЛ for this haa5 can be confusing in Cantonese
    because this дЄЛ is *not* homophonous with дЄЛ (haa6) meaning "down" or "go down".
    This is especially true in some of Williams' examples,
    where there is insufficient semantic context
    to disambiguate between haa5 and haa6 if дЄЛ is used
    (e.g. иІАеРУе†і vs иІАдЄЛе†і under $е†іcoeng4, and и©≥еРУ vs и©≥дЄЛ under $и©≥coeng4).
    Thus, for practical purposes, I have *not* normalised еРУ to дЄЛ.
  - However, there are separate haa5 that *are* exclusive to Cantonese;
    see the Cantonese entry below.
  - Williams' дЄАеРУеРМеОї: Corrected _(4)^tung_ (dung4) to _(4)t(')ung_ (tung4).
  - Williams' еХПеАЩеРУдљҐеЧї: Corrected _(2)ch(e/)_ (ze2) to _ch(e/)(3)_ (ze3).
    In modern Cantonese the final particle would be $еХЂze1 instead of the (now) dated $еЧїze3.
  ==
E
  ====
  - гАРеРУ-modifierгАС (haa5)
    ++
    1. Suffixed after an adjective that has been degree-modified by еєЊ "quite".
       The added suffix somewhat(?) lessens the degree.
       ==
       - дїКжЧ•еєЊеЗНеРУ (gam1 jat6 gei2 dung3 haa5): "[It's] quite cold today."
       - зҐЯй§ЄеєЊиЊ£еРУ (dip6 sung3 gei2 laat6 haa5): "[The] dish [is] quite spicy."
       ==
    ++
  - гАРеРУ-duringгАС (haa5, haa5-2)
    ++
    1. Suffixed after a reduplicated verb,
       before introducing an event that occurs during the action of the verb
       (i.e. after the action has started but before the action ought to cease).
       The (tone-unchanged) reading haa5 is strongly preferred
       when the reduplicated verb is tone~2.
       ==
       - и°Ми°МеРУиЕ≥иїЯ (haang4 haang4 haa5-2 goek3 jyun5): "In [the] middle of walking [I felt] weak-legged."
       - й£Яй£ЯеРУжГ≥еШФ (sik6 sik6 haa5 soeng2 au2): "In [the] middle of eating [I] wanted to vomit."
       - иђЫиђЫеРУеФФи®ШеЊЧеТЧ (gong2 gong2 haa5 m4 gei3 dak1 zo2): "In [the] middle of speaking [he] forgot [about it]."
       ==
    ++
